// EXPECT_RUNTIME_PANIC ensures failed: result >= 10
//
// Plan 140 Ф.4 (D24 amend), acceptance F1: an UNPROVEN `ensures` is checked at
// runtime in the RELEASE build (`--mode release`) and aborts fail-fast on
// violation.
//
// Note: should-abort test. Sole assertion is EXPECT_RUNTIME_PANIC (nonzero exit
// + structured `nova_contract_violation` message on stderr). No stdout assert:
// `abort()` does not flush libc stdout buffers.
//
// `at_least_ten` carries `ensures result >= 10` but its body just returns `x`
// unchanged, so the postcondition holds only for x >= 10. The contract is NOT
// statically provable for an arbitrary `x` (and not statically disprovable for
// every input — only for some), so the VerificationPipeline leaves it OUT of
// `proven_contracts` → codegen emits the `nova_contract_violation(
// NOVA_CONTRACT_POST, ...)` guard right before the function returns.
//
// `main` calls `at_least_ten(3)`, which returns 3 and violates the ensures. In
// release the POST guard fires → stderr message + abort() → nonzero exit. The
// companion positive case is t2 (a PROVABLE ensures is elided, zero-cost).
//
// `UNREACHABLE` is never printed because the postcondition abort terminates
// the process first.

module plan140.t3_ensures_release

fn at_least_ten(x int) -> int
    ensures result >= 10
=> x

fn main() Io -> () {
    ro _ = at_least_ten(3)
    println("UNREACHABLE")
}
